 {"id":"bd-177o","title":"update check changelog_diff is always None (TODO)","description":"# Task: Implement Changelog Diff

## Discovery
Found TODO comment in code review.

## Evidence
In `rch/src/update/check.rs` line 142:
```rust
changelog_diff: None, // TODO: Compute diff
```

The `UpdateInfo` struct has a `changelog_diff` field that is never populated.

## Current Behavior
When checking for updates, users see:
```
New version available: 1.1.0 (current: 1.0.0)
Run 'rch update' to update.
```

No information about what changed.

## Expected Behavior
```
New version available: 1.1.0 (current: 1.0.0)

Changes since 1.0.0:
  - Fixed fleet deploy command
  - Added checksum verification
  - Performance improvements

Run 'rch update' to update.
```

## Implementation Approach

### Option A: Parse CHANGELOG.md
1. Fetch CHANGELOG.md from GitHub
2. Extract entries between current and new version
3. Format for display

### Option B: Use GitHub Release Notes
1. Fetch release notes from GitHub releases API
2. Already structured per-version
3. May include contributor info

### Proposed Code
```rust
async fn fetch_changelog_diff(current: &str, new: &str) -> Option<String> {
    let url = format!(
        "https://api.github.com/repos/{}/{}/releases/tags/v{}",
        REPO_OWNER, REPO_NAME, new
    );

    let response: GithubRelease = reqwest::get(&url).await.ok()?.json().await.ok()?;

    // Format release body for terminal display
    Some(format_release_notes(&response.body))
}
```

## Files to Modify
- `rch/src/update/check.rs` - Implement changelog fetching
- `rch/src/update/mod.rs` - Display changelog in update check output

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `rch update --check` shows what changed
- [ ] Changelog is formatted nicely for terminal
- [ ] Gracefully handles missing changelog (just show version)
